Test setting up an alarm:
    1. Add an event to calendar a short amount of time in the future
    2. Open MBR app
    3. Navigate to events page
    4. Verify that the event is present
    5. Check the event and verify that it gets checked
    6. Navigate to the alarms page and verify that the event now has a scheduled alarm
    7. Verify that the alarm rings when its time passes

Test disabling a scheduled alarm:
    1. Add an event to calendar a short amount of time in the future
    2. Open MBR app
    3. Navigate to events page
    4. Verify that the event is present
    5. Check the event and verify that it gets checked
    6. Navigate to the alarms page and verify that the event now has a scheduled alarm
    7. Navigate back to the events page and un-check the checked event, verifying that it does get unselected
    8. Navigate back to the alarms page and verify that the even no longer has a scheduled alarm

Test adding an alarm with 2 hours of another will affect alarm time of the second:
    1. Add two events to calendar within two hours of each other
    2. Check the later event event
    3. Note the alarm time set for the event
    4. Check the first event
    5. Make sure the second event's alarm time has been updated

Test removing an alarm will affect the start time of the even after it if it is within two hours:
    1. Add two events to calendar within two hours of each other
    2. Check both events
    3. Note the start time of the second event
    4. Uncheck the first event
    5. Make sure the second event's alarm time has been updated

Test updating first alarm time with current location:
    1. Add an event to calendar
    2. Check the event
    3. Note the start time of the event
    4. Physically move to a distant enough place
    5. On start screen click button to update location for first event
    6. Make sure the first event's alarm has been updated
